.TH "capable_wrt_inode_uidgid" 9 "capable_wrt_inode_uidgid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
capable_wrt_inode_uidgid \- Check nsown_capable and uid and gid mapped
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" capable_wrt_inode_uidgid
.BI "(struct user_namespace *mnt_userns "  ","
.BI "const struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "int cap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mnt_userns" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "inode" 12
The inode in question
.IP "cap" 12
The capability in question
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return true if the current task has the given capability targeted at
its own user namespace and that the given inode's uid and gid are
mapped into the current user namespace.
